blueArcTitan.name: blueArcTitan

revisions.description: Obsolete FTP user and mount point objects, which are no longer to be reported by the agent.
Obsolete NVRAM objects, and re-implement in BLUEARC_SERVER_MIB.
Define objects for reporting FTP configuration, mount points, users and statistics. Obsolete NVRAM objects, and re-implement in a table indexed by Cluster Node.
Obsolete all quota template and quota objects, and re-implement them using Counter64 data types for usage and usage-limit objects.

virtualVolumeTitanNumber.name: virtualVolumeTitanNumber
virtualVolumeTitanNumber.description: The number of virtual volumes which are currently accessible. NOTE: a virtual volume is only accessible if its associated parent volume is mounted.

virtualVolumeTitanTable.name: virtualVolumeTitanTable
virtualVolumeTitanTable.description: A table containing information about each virtual volume. The number of entries in this table is given by the value of virtualVolumeTitanNumber.

virtualVolumeTitanSpanId.name: virtualVolumeTitanSpanId
virtualVolumeTitanSpanId.description: The parent device of the virtual volume. The device identified by a particular value of this index is the span underlying the volume hosting the Virtual Volume.

virtualVolumeTitanName.name: virtualVolumeTitanName
virtualVolumeTitanName.description: The name assigned to the virtual volume by a user for identification purposes.

virtualVolumeTitanPath.name: virtualVolumeTitanPath
virtualVolumeTitanPath.description: The path to the root of this Virtual Volume.

virtualVolumeTitanEmailNumber.name: virtualVolumeTitanEmailNumber
virtualVolumeTitanEmailNumber.description: The number of email addresses associated with this Virtual Volume.

virtualVolumeTitanQuotaNumber.name: virtualVolumeTitanQuotaNumber
virtualVolumeTitanQuotaNumber.description: The number of quotas associated with this Virtual Volume.

virtualVolumeTitanEmailTable.name: virtualVolumeTitanEmailTable
virtualVolumeTitanEmailTable.description: A table containing the email address associated with this Virtual Volume. The number of entries in this table is given by the value of virtualVolumeTitanEmailNumber, in virtualVolumeTitanTable.

virtualVolumeTitanEmailEntry.name: virtualVolumeTitanEmailEntry
virtualVolumeTitanEmailEntry.description: An email address associated with a Virtual Volume, which is uniquely identified by virtualVolumeTitanSpanId and virtualVolumeTitanName in virtualVolumeTitanTable.

virtualVolumeTitanEmailAddress.name: virtualVolumeTitanEmailAddress
virtualVolumeTitanEmailAddress.description: An email address associated with a Virtual Volume.

virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTemplateTable.name: virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTemplateTable
virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTemplateTable.description: A table containing quota templates associated with Virtual Volumes. The template is indexed by the values virtualVolumeTitanSpanId and virtualVolumeTitanTarget in virtualVolumeTitanTable, and the virtualVolumeQuotaTemplateTargetType. The two types of quota template are: user quota template, and group quota template. The templates define the default quota settings which will be used to create a Default Quota when a user or group begins to use the Virtual Volume. Once the default quota has been created, a user or group's quota may be modified, whence it will become an Explicit Quota. This object is now obsolete.

virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTemplateEntry.name: virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTemplateEntry
virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTemplateEntry.description: A quota template associated with a Virtual Volume. The template is indexed by the values virtualVolumeTitanSpanId and virtualVolumeTitanTarget in virtualVolumeTitanTable, and the virtualVolumeQuotaTemplateTargetType. This object is now obsolete.

virtualVolumeQuotaTemplateTargetType.name: virtualVolumeQuotaTemplateTargetType
virtualVolumeQuotaTemplateTargetType.description: The type of a Quota Template associated with a Virtual Volume. user(1) - a Quota Template for a user group(2) - a Quota Template for a group. This object is now obsolete.

virtualVolumeQuotaTemplateIgnoreWellKnow.name: virtualVolumeQuotaTemplateIgnoreWellKnownGroups
virtualVolumeQuotaTemplateIgnoreWellKnow.description: Should this Quota Template generate a quota for well-known groups. A well-known group would be a group to which many or all of the potential users belong. It may be desired to ignore such a group because a default quota generated would quickly reach usage or file-count thresholds, and cause events to be logged unnecessarily. A value notapplicable(3) will be set if the row in the table relates to a User Quota Template. This object is now obsolete.

virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTemplateUsageLimi.name: virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTemplateUsageLimit
virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTemplateUsageLimi.description: The upper limit set for usage of space in the quota. This object is now obsolete.

virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTemplateUsageHard.name: virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTemplateUsageHardLimit
virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTemplateUsageHard.description: Whether the upper limit for usage on the quota is a hard limit. soft(1) - not a hard limit. hard(2) - a hard limit. This object is now obsolete.

virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTemplateUsageRese.name: virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTemplateUsageReset
virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTemplateUsageRese.description: When a warning limit for usage has been reached, a warning event will not be logged again until the use of the quota has first dropped back to the reset value. This object is now obsolete.

virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTemplateUsageWarn.name: virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTemplateUsageWarning

virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTemplateUsageCrit.name: virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTemplateUsageCritical

virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTable.name: virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTable
virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTable.description: A table containing quotas associated with Virtual Volumes. The quotas are indexed by the values virtualVolumeTitanSpanId and virtualVolumeTitanTarget in virtualVolumeTitanTable, and the quota name. This object is now obsolete.

virtualVolumeTitanQuotaEntry.name: virtualVolumeTitanQuotaEntry
virtualVolumeTitanQuotaEntry.description: Information about a quota. This object is now obsolete.

virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTarget.name: virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTarget
virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTarget.description: The target of a quota. If the quota is a Virtual Volume quota (i.e. tracking usage of the entire Virtual Volume, regardless of the user of group) then the target will be 'Virtual Volume Quota'. A User Quota will have a target comprised of the user's domain and user name, in the form <domain>\<user>. A Group quota target will consist of the group's domain and group name, in the form <domain>\<group>. This object is now obsolete.

virtualVolumeTitanQuotaType.name: virtualVolumeTitanQuotaType
virtualVolumeTitanQuotaType.description: Indicates whether the quota is a default or explicit quota. default(1) - the quota has been created automatically using the default values for the Virtual Volume. explicit(2) - the quota has been created explicitly using user-defined values. This object is now obsolete.

virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTargetType.name: virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTargetType
virtualVolumeTitanQuotaTargetType.description: Indicates whether the scope of the quota's tracking. user(1) - the quota is tracking a single user's use of the Virtual Volume. group(2) - the quota is tracking a group's use of the Virtual Volume. virtualvolume(3) - the quota is tracking the use of the entire Virtual Volume. This object is now obsolete.

nvramSize.name: nvramSize
nvramSize.description: The total size of nvram. If no formatted or mounted volume is found, or if nvram is not supported, this value will be reported as zero. This object is obsolete, and is re-implemented in nvramPoolTable.

nvramMaximumUsed.name: nvramMaximumUsed
nvramMaximumUsed.description: The maximum amount of nvram used. If no formatted or mounted volume is found, or if nvram is not supported, this value will be reported as zero. This object is obsolete, and is re-implemented in nvramPoolTable.

nvramTotalCurrentUsage.name: nvramTotalCurrentUsage
nvramTotalCurrentUsage.description: The amount of nvram currently in use. If no formatted or mounted volume is found, or if nvram is not supported, this value will be reported as zero. This object is obsolete, and is re-implemented in nvramPoolTable.

nvramNumber.name: nvramNumber
nvramNumber.description: The number of volumes with NVRAM statistics.

nvramTable.name: nvramTable
nvramTable.description: A table of NVRAM data for a given volume.

nvramEntry.name: nvramEntry
nvramEntry.description: Information about NVRAM on a given volume. The volume must be formatted, mounted, and NVRAM must be supported.

spanId.name: spanId
spanId.description: The id of the Span hosting the volume with which the NVRAM is associated.

nvramCurrentUsage.name: nvramCurrentUsage
nvramCurrentUsage.description: The amount of NVRAM currently in use for this volume.

nvramNumberCheckpoints.name: nvramNumberCheckpoints
nvramNumberCheckpoints.description: The total number of checkpoints which have occurred for the NVRAM assigned to this volume.

nvramNumberActivityCheckpoints.name: nvramNumberActivityCheckpoints
nvramNumberActivityCheckpoints.description: The number of checkpoints which have occurred for the NVRAM assigned to this volume as a result of file system activity (i.e. not timed checkpoints.

nvramPoolTable.name: nvramPoolTable
nvramPoolTable.description: A table of NVRAM data for a given Cluster Node.

nvramPoolEntry.name: nvramPoolEntry
nvramPoolEntry.description: Information about NVRAM on a given Cluster Node.

clusterNodeId.name: clusterNodeId
clusterNodeId.description: The ID of the cluster node for which these pool statistics are reported.

nvramPoolSize.name: nvramPoolSize
nvramPoolSize.description: The total size of nvram. If no formatted or mounted volume is found, or if nvram is not supported, this value will be reported as zero.

nvramPoolMaximumUsed.name: nvramPoolMaximumUsed
nvramPoolMaximumUsed.description: The maximum amount of nvram used. If no formatted or mounted volume is found, or if nvram is not supported, this value will be reported as zero.

nvramPoolTotalCurrentUsage.name: nvramPoolTotalCurrentUsage
nvramPoolTotalCurrentUsage.description: The amount of nvram currently in use. If no formatted or mounted volume is found, or if nvram is not supported, this value will be reported as zero.

packageNumber.name: packageNumber

packageTable.description: A table containing details of the packages available in flash.

packageEntry.name: packageEntry
packageEntry.description: Information about the packages in flash.

packageDate.name: packageDate
packageDate.description: The date on which the package was uploaded.

packageSize.name: packageSize
packageSize.description: The size of the package in bytes.

packageDefault.name: packageDefault
packageDefault.description: Whether the package is the default package. The default package is the package which will be loaded when the server is rebooted. default(1) - the default package. notdefault(2) - not the default package.

packageCurrent.name: packageCurrent
packageCurrent.description: Whether the package is the current package. The current package is the package which was loaded when the server was rebooted. current(1) - the current package. notcurrent(2) - not the current package.

packageFreeSpace.name: packageFreeSpace
packageFreeSpace.description: The amount of available flash file-space, in bytes.

ftpConfigServiceEnabled.name: ftpConfigServiceEnabled
ftpConfigServiceEnabled.description: Indicates whether the FTP service is enabled. enabled(1) - the service is enabled disabled(2) - the service is disabled unknown(3) - the status of the service cannot be determined. This object is now obsolete.

ftpConfigServiceMaxUsers.name: ftpConfigServiceMaxUsers
ftpConfigServiceMaxUsers.description: The maximum number of FTP users the service will allow. This object is now obsolete.

ftpConfigNTPasswordEnabled.name: ftpConfigNTPasswordEnabled
ftpConfigNTPasswordEnabled.description: Indicates whether FTP uses NT password authentication. enabled(1) - NT security is enabled disabled(2) - NT security is disabled notavailable(3) - NT security is not available unknown(4) - the status of NT security cannot be determined. This object is now obsolete.

ftpConfigNISPasswordEnabled.name: ftpConfigNISPasswordEnabled
ftpConfigNISPasswordEnabled.description: Indicates whether FTP uses NIS password authentication. enabled(1) - NIS security is enabled disabled(2) - NIS security is disabled notavailable(3) - NIS security is not available unknown(4) - the status of NIS security cannot be determined. This object is now obsolete.
